        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 12:56AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1256 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bloomington, or near McFaddin, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Victoria, Guadalupe, Victoria Colony Creek Country Club, Dacosta,
Wood Hi, Bloomington, Victoria Detar Hospital North, Victoria
Riverside Park, Placedo, Victoria College, Victoria Mall, Saxet
Lakes, Brentwood Subdivision, Victoria Regional Airport, Telferner,
Downtown Victoria, and Ball Airport Area.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 59 between mile markers 628 and 642.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 572 and 576, and between mile
markers 586 and 594.
US Highway 87 between mile markers 808 and 824.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
